    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab><persName ref="#people/225" key="#Count">Ildeprandus</persName> in Dei
                        nomine <rs key="#Count">comes</rs>, filio <persName ref="#people/3307">bone
                            memorie Eribrandi</persName> permuta beni con <persName
                            ref="#people/214" key="#Bishops">Gherardus</persName> gratia Dei huius
                        sancte Lucane ecclesie humilis <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> (…).
                        Ildebrando cede a Gherardo: ad pars ipsius <rs key="#Mother_churches"
                            >episcopatui</rs> vestri <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/68"
                            key="#Mother_churches">Sancti Martini</orgName>, id est una <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions">petia de terra</rs> mea illa, quam
                        abeo in loco ubi dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions">Cafagio Alisi</placeName>,
                        qui <rs key="#Confinia">uno capo tenet</rs> in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs> qui fuit <persName key="#Deacons #Other_clerics">quondam
                                <name ref="Rodegarius">R[ode]garii</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons #Other_clerics">diaconi clerici</rs>, aliquantum in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <persName ref="#people/3308">Eribrandi</persName> germano meo, alio capo
                        tenet in <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <persName><name ref="Gausbrandus">Chausiprandi</name> de <placeName
                                ref="#places/703">Versiciano</placeName></persName>, lato uno tenet
                        in <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <persName><name ref="Iohannes">Iohannis</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Rofredus">Roffridi</name></persName>, alio lato tenet in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions">Sancti Petri</orgName>; simula
                        et una <rs key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions">petia de terra</rs> mea in ipso
                        loco ad <placeName key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Cafagia"><rs
                                key="#Cafagia">Cafagio</rs>
                            <persName key="#Cafagia"><name ref="Alisso"
                            >Alisi</name></persName></placeName>, prope suprascripta terra, petia
                        ipsa in integrum; simul et dare videor ad pars ipsius episcopatui una alia
                            <rs key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions">petia de terra</rs> mea in loco
                            <placeName
                            key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Roads"
                            ref="#places/395">Rocta</placeName>, qui capo uno tenet in <rs
                            key="#Roads">via</rs>, alio capo tenet in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs> de <persName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #childOf"
                                ><rs key="#childOf">filii</rs> quondam <name ref="Ardo"
                            >Ardi</name></persName>, lato uno tenet in <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs>
                        <persName><name ref="Roppaldus">Roppaldi</name></persName>, alio lato tenet
                        in <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> de <persName
                            key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #childOf"><rs key="#childOf"
                                >filii</rs> quondam <name ref="Adrefunsus"
                            >Atrifusi</name></persName>; simul et una alia <rs
                            key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions">petia de terra</rs> mea illa quas abeo
                        in ipso loco <placeName
                            key="#Confinia #Petiae #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Roads"
                            ref="#places/395">Rocta</placeName>, qui capo uno cum uno lato tenet in
                            <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <persName key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions"><name ref="Sisemundus"
                                >Sisemundi</name></persName>, alio capo cum alio lato tenet in terra
                        Roppaldi; suprascripte petie de terra (…) una cum cesis et omnibus arboribus
                        suis (…). Riceve in cambio: una <rs key="#Petiae #Landed_possessions">petia
                            de terra</rs> in loco <placeName ref="#places/60"
                            key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Object #Redistributive #Inflow"
                            >Mari&lt;lla></placeName> pertinens ipsius <rs key="#Mother_churches"
                            >episcopatui</rs> vestro <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/68"
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Outflow #Mother_churches">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName>, qui <rs key="#Confinia">uno capo tenet</rs> in <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> de <persName
                            key="#Confinia #Landed_possessions #childOf"><rs key="#childOf"
                                >filii</rs> quondam <name ref="Danihel">Dani[el]</name></persName>,
                        alio capo tenet in <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs> mea qui supra
                        Ildeprando comes, lato uno tenet in <rs key="#Rivers">rivo Frasula</rs>,
                        alio lato tenet in <rs key="#Roads">via publica</rs>; suprascripta petia de
                        terra (…) una cum cesis et omnibus arboribus suis (…). Unde et super hanc
                        comutationem tu qui supra <persName ref="#people/214" key="#Bishops"
                            >Gherardus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> direxisti <rs
                            key="#Missus_of_other_public_authorities #Bishops">missos tuos</rs>, i
                        sunt <persName key="#Witness #Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Alateus">Alateo</name></persName> et <persName
                            key="#Witness #Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name ref="Ermiteus"
                                >Ermiteo</name></persName> ; et <persName ref="#people/1514"
                            key="#Marquis/duke">Adalbertus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">dux</rs> direxit <rs
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Missus_of_other_public_authorities">missos
                        suos</rs>, id est <persName
                            key="#Witness #Missus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Agilmannus">Aggelmanno</name></persName> , qui ambulaverunt et
                        previderunt adque renuntiaverunt quod meliorata res dedi ad parte ipsius
                        episcopatui quam recepisse, ut magis inter nos omni tempore hanc comutatio
                        firma et stabile permaneat (…). Pena in duplum. <persName
                            key="#Writer #Witness #Notary"><name ref="Rofredus"
                            >Roffridi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> scrive due <rs key="#Commutatio"
                            >cartulas</rs>. Actum <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Churches #Mother_churches #Bishops">Luca</placeName>. </ab>
                    <ab>Oltre ai missi sottoscrivono come <rs key="#Witness">testimoni</rs>:
                            <persName key="#Witness #Scabini"><name ref="Iohannes"
                            >Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Scabini">schabinus</rs>, <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Sigefredus">Sichifridi</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness"><name ref="Walbrandus">Vualprando</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Eriteus">Eriteo</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Sicardus"
                            >Sicherado</name></persName>, <persName key="#Witness #Notary"><name
                                ref="Lopo">Lopo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>ChLA, 83, n. 19, pp. 66-69; MDL, 5/2, n. 835, pp. 508-509</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Sottoscrizioni autografe: Ildiprandus comes (autore), Alateo (misso), Ermiteo
                    (misso), Iohannes schabinus, Sichifridi, Vualprando, Eriteo, Sicherado, Lopo
                    notarius, Roffridi notarius (scrittore). Sottoscrizioni con
                        <foreign>Signa</foreign>: Aggelmanno (misso). Note tergali: di mano del
                    secolo X, con marcate inflessioni cancelleresche e uso di litterae elongatae:
                        <foreign>viganium de Hildiprando com(es)</foreign>; di mano dell’XI:
                        <foreign>iste vig(aneum) p(re) nimia vetustate seu p(er) longitudine
                        t(em)poru(m) carte cognitione locor(um)</foreign>; di altra mano dell’XI:
                        <foreign>in Cafagio Alisi et in Rotta</foreign>; di seguito, a completamento
                    di questa, di mano del XII secolo: <foreign>et Capa(n)nore</foreign>.</p>
            </div>
